Ask HN: Unique or interesting experiences for software developers?
text:
I have a friend that will be serving in Antarctica as part of a science program and it got me wondering what unique or rare opportunities there might be for software developers.

By this, I don't just mean "cool jobs", but more so opportunities that are meant to be constrained by time, location, or scope for some specific purpose. An example might be the US digital service program for US citizens, which had (has?) a 1 year term-limited service that software developers could join to help modernize government technological services.

Ask HN: What Is Readable Code?
text:
“DRY code is readable” “no WET code is readable” “Go is readable” “no Go is verbose”

What makes code readable? I feel like this word is borderline synonymous with “I like this thing”. We all know code is read more than written, so readability matters, but does anyone actually know what makes it easier to read and understand?
